## When to use this pattern

Use this pattern when a teacher is eligible for your service if they teach or
taught one or more of a small selection of subjects.

## When not to use this pattern

Do not use this pattern when you need to ask a teacher which subjects they teach
from a large selection of subjects. Instead consider alternative methods such
as a [search option](https://github.com/alphagov/govuk-design-system-backlog/issues/88)
or [text input](https://design-system.service.gov.uk/components/text-input/).

## How it works

This is a unique pattern which combines the use of checkboxes with a single
radio button separated by a [text divider](https://design-system.service.gov.uk/components/radios/#radio-items-with-a-text-divider).

- When a user selects one or more checkboxes, the radio button is unselected.
- When a user selects the radio button, all checkboxes are unselected.
- Allow users to flag themselves as ineligible by selecting 'I did not teach
  any of these subjects' then explain why on the 'ineligible screen'.

### Asking within a limited timeframe

It may be useful to ask this question in relation to a limited timeframe such as
the last academic year. When doing this:

- be clear about the timeframe in question and use the correct [date formats](https://www.gov.uk/guidance/style-guide/a-to-z-of-gov-uk-style#dates)
- include any other information like the school name if you've already asked for this

